Ad Text:
Join a high-profile organisation embarking on a major customer data transformation designed to create a single, trusted view of the customer and enable personalised experiences across digital and marketing channels.

We're looking for a Data Business Analyst with a strong background in data-driven projects who can confidently bridge business needs with technical delivery. You'll play a key role in shaping data models, integrations, and customer insights capabilities that directly influence engagement, loyalty, and marketing effectiveness.

Purpose of the Role:
The Data Business Analyst (BA) will play a key role in delivering a customer data platform (CDP) initiative aimed at establishing a single, trusted view of the customer. This role will bridge business needs and technical delivery, ensuring that data-driven insights and marketing capabilities,such as segmentation, personalisation, and preferences management-are effectively supported by a robust data foundation.

What you'll be doing:

Lead workshops with cross-functional stakeholders to define and document business and functional requirements.

Translate marketing and customer experience goals into clear data and integration requirements.

Partner with Data Engineers and Architects to deliver within an Azure-based data ecosystem.

Support testing and validation across data pipelines, models, and transformations.

Collaborate with external vendors to align technical delivery and resolve integration challenges.

What you'll bring:

Proven experience as a Business Analyst on data-centric or customer analytics projects.

Solid understanding of data models, pipelines, and SQL (ideally within Azure environments such as Data Factory or Synapse).

Working knowledge of Single Customer View (SCV), Customer 360, or Customer Data Platforms (CDP).

Experience supporting marketing or personalisation use cases such as segmentation or audience targeting.

Excellent communication skills and the ability to operate between business, data, and technical teams.

This is a great opportunity to contribute to a strategic data initiative with strong executive visibility, while working alongside a highly capable Data & Analytics team in a flexible, hybrid environment.

This role is 3 days PW in office.

$700 PD Inclusive of Super - 6 Months initial contract plus extensions

Company Description

Nine is Australia’s largest locally owned media company. Working at Nine, you’ll have access to a unique range of experiences and opportunities, helping drive the success of the country’s most trusted television, radio, digital and publishing brands. 

Our content reaches almost every Australian - meaning what we do has real impact. We bring people together, celebrate the big moments, and capture the everyday ones.

Some of our most beloved brands have been part of Australian life for generations, and others - new on the scene - have already found their place firmly in our lives. We’re evolving and we need people like you to bring new ideas, innovate and make your mark.

Job Description

Reporting to the AI Product Lead, you will work hand-in-hand with data scientists, engineers, product managers and business stakeholders to ensure the seamless and efficient implementation of AI capabilities across Nine's diverse portfolio. This role is crucial for translating high-level product strategies into actionable, component-level technical diagrams and documentation, ensuring a clear and shared understanding for all technical and non-technical stakeholders.

Day to day you will:

Work closely with business and technical stakeholders to identify requirements and workflow for AI projects, map business process flows, gather detailed technical requirements, and translate them into specifications for development teams. Create and maintain a Business Requirements Document (BRD) and other project-related documentation. 
Support the AI product lifecycle by collaborating with the AI Product Lead to ensure technical documentation is aligned with the product roadmap and delivery timelines. 
Serve as a key communication link, ensuring that data scientists and engineers have a clear understanding of the project's technical requirements and business context. 
Testing and Quality Assurance: Participate in creating test plans, developing test cases, and executing user acceptance testing (UAT). Validate that the final product meets the documented requirements and effectively solves the business problem. 
Proactively identify and recommend improvements to existing processes and methodologies to enhance the efficiency of AI project implementation. 
Qualifications

What you’ll bring:

3+ years experience as a technical business analyst, process analyst, or similar.
Proven experience mapping and documenting technical processes, especially in data-centric projects.
Familiarity with AI/ML project lifecycles.
Exceptional analytical and problem-solving skills with strong technical documentation and diagramming abilities.
Excellent communication and stakeholder management skills to bridge technical and business teams.
Understanding of data flows, APIs, and familiarity with agile development methodologies.
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, IT, Engineering, or a related quantitative field; business analysis or process management certifications are a plus.
Additional Information

How we work

At Nine, our flexible work options vary by role and team. Depending on the position, this may include flexible hours, hybrid work, or part-time arrangements. We welcome discussing your flexibility needs during the hiring process - just ask the Talent Acquisition team. 

Our employee benefits include:

18 weeks paid parental leave with no distinction between primary and secondary carers.
Access to 'Employee Exclusives' program - a way of getting closer to our incredible brands, offering unique experiences, behind-the-scenes access, and awesome perks.
Digital newspaper subscription to our mastheads.
Annual gift voucher for Stan subscription.

More info at Nine Careers.

Our Commitment to Diversity and Inclusion:

We're committed to a safe, respectful and inclusive Nine. From day one, you'll be encouraged to bring your whole self to work and will be supported to perform at your best.

We encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander people, people with disabilities, and of all ages, genders, nationalities, backgrounds and cultures as we recognise the importance and value of diverse perspectives. Should you require any adjustments to the recruitment process, please advise us when you apply.

Work rights: Please note to apply for this role you must already have the right to lawfully work and live in Australia.

About Us

At Sportsbet, we’re all about bringing excitement to life for our 2.4 million customers. As part of the global Flutter Group, we’re a tight-knit team of 1,300 in Melbourne, Sydney, and Darwin, passionate about challenging the status quo. We’re proud to be recognized as one of LinkedIn’s Top 25 Companies and one of the Top 10 Workplaces for Women. We’re an inclusive employer who celebrates diversity and is committed to helping you thrive. Whether you’re looking for flexibility, career growth, or a supportive environment, we’re here to help you succeed.

Committed To Responsible Gambling

Our commitment to responsible gambling is genuine and demonstrated through the wide range of responsible gambling initiatives and tools. We’re proud to be the leaders in responsible gambling in our industry, not just locally, but globally.

The Team

In Data Science we work collaboratively with teams across the organisation to create and evolve end to end solutions that have Data Science at their core. From sports modelling to product personalisation, our team thrives on unleashing the power of data to improve the quality, speed and complexity of the decisions and actions they drive. Our models not only power many of the products our customers get to enjoy, but they also take many of our internal processes to the next level.

We care for things we have built and look at ways to continuously improve them; but we also love to innovate. We are known pioneers and have introduced a number of world first ML-driven customer-facing products. They come from insights, experience but often, just from someone thinking outside of the box – we play a key role in exploring these ideas and making them a reality. Not only we innovate with product, but also in the way we build, develop, deploy and maintain our solutions and how we leverage evolving platforms partnerships.

The Role

Joining the Customer Growth team, the duties and responsibilities include:

Work with key stakeholders from across the business to ensure that business requirements are explored, understood and considered when designing and building models.
Communicate complex technical information in an easy-to-understand way to keep stakeholders engaged and aligned to progress.
Design and deploy models in accordance with MLOps best principles to deliver high quality and supportable products.
Contribute in designing ways to test, track and communicate the ongoing impact of the solutions we deliver.

You - some of the talents we’re looking to find:

Experience with conceiving, designing, building, deploying and monitoring machine learning models, with an excellent eye for detail.
Commercially minded – track record of unlocking data to drive commercial value.
Broad knowledge of statistical and computational methods for identifying patterns, extracting insights, and making predictions from complex datasets.
Strong programming skills (e.g. proficient in Python, R etc with experience in Spark and Databricks a plus).
Degree in a quantitative discipline (e.g. Mathematics, Statistics, Physics, Computer Science).
Good communication skills with the ability to explain complex concepts to a wide variety of audiences, both verbally and written.

Why You’ll Love Working Here

Along with a competitive salary and generous performance-based bonus, here’s some of our other benefits:
25 days annual leave (plus flexible working options)
$1050 work-from-home allowance
Access to outstanding career development programs, including expert-led internal training and external learning opportunities
Onsite concierge services, free meals, social events and access to the Sportsbet Salon
Generous parental leave and return-to-work benefits
Hack Days: Participate in our hack days, where creativity and collaboration lead to exciting new ideas and projects.

What’s the Green Tick Feeling?

Well, it’s different for everyone, yet unites us all. It’s the feeling you get when you succeed, no matter what success looks like to you. It could be developing your career, it could be working on an industry leading project, or it could be making it to school pick up in time. It's all the little and big things that make you feel like you’re thriving when working at Sportsbet.

We’re an inclusive employer who welcomes you for who you are, as you are – so, if you require adjustments to the recruitment process, please let us know in your application. We also know flex means different things to different people, so let us know how we can support you to be your best.

We review applications quickly, so apply soon! Check out our Life@Sportsbet Instagram, LinkedIn, and careers website for more about our inclusive culture.

Ready for your Green Tick Feeling? Apply now.

About BHP 


At BHP we support our people to grow, learn, develop their skills and reach their potential. With a global portfolio of operations, we offer a diverse and inclusive environment with extraordinary career opportunities. Our strategy is to focus on creating a safe work environment where our employees feel strongly connected to our values and objectives, and where the capability of our people is key to our success.

Come and be a part of this success.

About the Role


BHP’s Value Engineering (VE) team is focused on maximising value-adding opportunities across BHP by leveraging skills in the Technical Function to deliver incremental, step change and innovative solutions. 

 
Reporting to the Manager Value Analytics for Minerals Australia, you will be part of a team of enthusiastic data practitioners working on performance improvement projects that focus on maximising value opportunities and performance across the value chain, through the application of data, operational and engineering expertise. You will be working collaboratively alongside site operations, business subject matter experts, data analytics professionals and other VE team members. 

 
In this role, you will: 

Provide technical team leadership 
Lead analysis projects 
Build working relationships with the BHP data community 
Lead the identification of business requirements to address stakeholder problems 
Document, explain and present analysis solutions to both technical and senior business stakeholders 
Mentor other team members in technical leadership 

The successful candidate will be able to work within a team environment, and will possess strong problem-solving skills, a collaborative mindset and be passionate about delivering extraordinary results with a focus on safety and continuous improvement. 

This is a Brisbane based role working Monday to Friday. Flexible work arrangements will be offered. 

About You


We are ideally seeking candidates who can demonstrate the following: 

Experience providing technical leadership to your team to help solve problems and streamline analysis. 
Experience delivering performance improvement solutions for business problems. This includes applying data analysis, statistical analysis, and machine learning techniques to generate business value while maintaining a practical and strategic focus 
Experience in applying industry standard analysis tools and approaches. This includes data platforms, programming languages and data analysis technologies 
Strong presentation and communication skills. You can influence stakeholders within different areas of expertise 
Experience in Mining, resource industry or equivalent heavy industries 

Other highly regarded skills include experience in: 

Engineering consulting and/or management consulting 
Managing projects 
Agile teams
About Our Process 


At BHP, we are committed to employing individuals who align with the BHP Charter Values and meet the requirements of the role. As part of the recruitment process, there are a number of checks which may be conducted to demonstrate applicants suitability for a role including police / criminal background checks, medical, drug and alcohol testing, due diligence checks, right to work checks, and/or reference checks. 

If you are already employed directly by BHP, please log in using your BHP email address or apply via our internal jobs portal. 

Supporting a Diverse Workforce  
 


The size, stability and magnitude of our business not only provides significant opportunity for professional development, but also attractive salary packages with performance-based bonuses and a best-in-class employee share program. We know there are many aspects of our employees' lives that are important, and work is only one of these, so we offer benefits to enable your work to fit with your life. These benefits include flexible working options, a generous paid parental leave policy, other extended leave entitlements and parent rooms.  

At BHP, we know that we are strengthened by diversity. We are an Equal Opportunity employer that is committed to making BHP a safe and inclusive workplace where everyone can thrive and be at their best every day. We are focused on creating a workforce that’s more diverse and represents the communities where we work and live, providing a work environment in which everyone is included, treated fairly and with respect. We are an Equal Opportunity employer and recognise that true diversity includes gender, age, race, disability status, sexual orientation, religion, neurodiversity, education levels, and many more aspects of your identity.

BHP is committed to providing a recruitment process that is fair, equitable and accessible for all. If you have a disability, we know that it may be helpful for us to adjust our process to make it equitable for your individual situation. If you would like to reach out to someone about your situation and our recruitment process, please email us at inclusion@bhp.com.

Our Organisation
  
Since 1925, ESSSuper and the funds before it have served the Victorian State Government, its employer agencies and their employees.
  
We administer the State's statutory defined benefit superannuation funds and obligations. Additionally, we administer accumulation-style products such as the ESSSuper Accumulation Plan and account-based Income Streams.
  
Our mission is to grow and protect our members' superannuation and support them throughout their lives.
With around 124,500 members holding over $37 billion in defined benefit and accumulation net assets (as at 30 June 2024), we're well-positioned to continue serving our members for years to come.
  
Position Description
  
As ESSSuper continues to grow and evolve, data is a key contributor to making sound business decisions.
  
The Data Governance Manager role is accountable for embedding and scaling the data governance framework across business units, enhancing data ownership, and operationalising data governance policies and standards being developed as a part of our multiyear data governance program.
  
  
Roles and Responsibilities

As Manager of Data Governance, you purpose will be to execute and embed the organisation’s data governance framework by ensuring governance practices meet standards such as VPDSS and APRA requirements.
You will lead the operational rollout of data governance policies, data quality standards, metadata management and stewardship practices.
Work closely with Data Engineering team, Risk, Compliance, Legal and business teams to tackle data related risks and support audit activities.
Represent data governance at various data governance councils, working groups and forums with stakeholders from Finance, Risk, IT, People & Culture and Operations.
Develop training programs for data stewards and business users to help promote data literacy and awareness across the organisation through targeted training, communication
  
  
  
What we’re looking for
  
To be considered for this role you will have a minimum 5+ years’ experience in data governance, data management, or in comparable regulatory data roles, experience in financial services environment is highly regarded.
You will be familiar with data management standards such as DAMA-DMBOK and have demonstrated experience implementing data governance frameworks and scaling practices across complex organisations
While not essential certification in Data Governance or Data Management (e.g., CDMP, DAMA) will be favourably viewed.
As a key player in implementing and promoting data governance you will also have a well strong communication skills and be able to manage up and down as the project requires.
ESSSuper is a supportive and positive environment and we hope that you are someone who can help enhance this with both your attitude and technical expertise.
  
  
What we offer
  
IMPACT - Our work has meaning, we serve the people who serve the community. We are passionate about serving our members and supporting them in getting the best possible superannuation and retirement outcomes.
  
DEVELOPMENT - We foster achievement through the development of our people. Focusing on building expertise and agility creates professional growth opportunities for our people and ensures that we are equipped to rise to the challenges of the future.
  
FLEXIBILITY – Our benefits and work practices promote the health and wellbeing of our people. We value a supportive and inclusive environment.
  
RELATIONSHIPS - Being part a small organisation within a dynamic sector draws people to ESSSuper, the supportive work environment keeps them here. We build strong relationships and collaborate to continually strengthen the experience of our members.
  
  
ESSSuper is an equal opportunity employer, we value diversity and inclusion, and we are committed to the attraction, retention and development of all people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation and disability.

About the Role

As the Data Ops Manager, you will lead the team responsible for the ongoing operation, optimisation, and continuous improvement of icare’s modern data platform across AWS and Snowflake & BI applications. You will play a critical role in ensuring platform performance, data reliability, and operational excellence – while driving a culture of proactive improvements and automation.

You will be a key enabler of downstream functions like Insights and CX, working closely with engineering, reporting, and governance teams to ensure seamless, trusted, and scalable data delivery. The role combines strong technical depth with people leadership, platform optimisation, and cross-team influence.

Benefits

A corporate wellbeing program with subsidised gym membership, free flu vaccinations and health check programs
Comprehensive learning and development support aligned to icare’s Core Capabilities.
Our People Awards - On-the-spot Recognition, Quarterly Values Awards & Our People Annual Awards
Access to our Employee Assistance Program

Duties

It’s an exciting time at icare where no two days are the same; as a Manager, Data Operations you will:

Lead the Data Ops team to monitor, operate, and continuously enhance icare’s cloud-based data platform.
Oversee platform health, cost, security, and performance across Snowflake, AWS Glue, S3, and supporting components.
Own and manage operational support processes (L2/L3), issue resolution workflows, and incident response procedure.
Implement and refine platform monitoring, alerting, and observability frameworks.
Work with key stakeholders across schemes to design and agree on key SLAs for data delivery and ensure they are delivered, tracked and communicated via weekly and monthly data operations report.
Drive a Continuous Improvement (CI) agenda, including:
Identifying and executing performance tuning opportunities (pipelines, queries, models).
Automating manual processes across monitoring, validation, and maintenance.
Leading the CI backlog and prioritising enhancement opportunities with stakeholders.
Collaborate with Data Platform Engineering to embed best practices from CI learnings into reusable pattern and platform design.
Contribute operational knowledge around the impact of change on data operations and ensure delivered risk are identified and communicated with programs
Influence and guide reporting/analytics teams (Performance Monitoring & Insights) on refresh optimisation and data model efficiency.
Support release and deployment processes in collaboration with DevOps Engineers.
Manage platform documentation, knowledge sharing, and technical uplift across the team.
Support the team’s evolution toward Agile ways of working and service line alignment.

Team Leadership

Coach and develop a high-performing team including Data Ops Analysts, Snowflake Specialists, AWS Specialists, and Ops Leads
Foster a culture of curiosity, ownership, and data reliability.
Collaborate with stakeholders across technology, transformation, reporting, CX, and governance functions.

Skills & Experience

7+ years in data operations, platform support or engineering
Proven experience leading DataOps or DevOps in cloud-based data environments
Demonstrated track record in operational support (L2/L3), platform optimisation, and incident management
Experience driving and delivering continuous improvement initiatives across data and analytics functions
Strong technical knowledge of data platforms (Snowflake, AWS or similar)
Proficiency in CI/CD, orchestration, and automation tooling
Solid understanding of performance tuning, pipeline monitoring, and query optimisation
Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills
Experience in public sector, insurance, or highly regulated industries
Exposure to Agile delivery environments and service-line aligned operating models
Knowledge of observability frameworks and data quality tooling (e.g. Great Expectations, OpenLineage)
Familiarity with data governance principles and data cataloguing
Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Information Systems, Engineering, or related field
Pre-Employment Checks
Relevant certifications (e.g. Snowflake, AWS, Dev/DataOps)
Post graduate qualifications in Data, Analytics or Technology Management

We are looking for an experienced and analytical Business Analyst to support the implementation and continuous improvement of IT Operational and Service Management processes. A key focus of this role is applying knowledge of Service Integration and Management (SIAM) principles to ensure cohesive service delivery across multiple internal and external service providers.

Working at the intersection of business and technology, you will engage stakeholders, gather and refine requirements, and translate these into effective solutions that align with ITSM and SIAM best practices. This is an exciting opportunity to help shape and optimise service delivery in a complex, multi-supplier environment.

1 x 12 month opportunity available. 

 

Key Responsibilities

Engage with stakeholders to gather, refine, and document requirements using interviews, workshops, workflow analysis, and more

Conduct business process reviews and identify opportunities for improvement or automation

Evaluate proposed system solutions with developers to ensure alignment with business and service expectations

Prepare and execute test plans and scripts, working closely with the Test Manager to ensure quality delivery

Document business requirements, process flows, user stories, and system specifications

Collaborate with subject matter experts to ensure solution design supports SIAM-aligned service integration

Analyse data relationships, service dependencies, and communication flows across multiple service providers

Recommend and assess new systems or features to improve multi-vendor service outcomes

Support the design and optimisation of end-to-end service delivery models under SIAM governance

Develop comprehensive documentation, user guides, and training materials

Contribute to the evaluation and implementation of new tools and technologies

Provide accurate and timely reporting to management and project stakeholders

 

Skills & Experience Required

5+ years’ experience as a Business Analyst within IT Operations or Service Delivery

Proven experience in Service Integration and Management (SIAM) environments

Strong understanding of multi-supplier service management models, service boundaries, and interface points

Experience working with service management frameworks such as ITIL and SIAM

Ability to document and analyse end-to-end services, identifying integration points and process gaps

Skilled in functional business analysis, including requirements elicitation and process automation

Excellent communication skills with experience facilitating workshops and stakeholder discussions

Demonstrated ability to bridge business needs and technical solutions

Background:

This Department plays a fundamental role underpinning the Australian economy by maintaining and regulating Australia’s measurement system, developing and maintaining national measurement standards, and delivering world-class measurement products and client services. 

Measurement is integral to a successful economy and to the progress of innovation and science. The work supports the productivity and growth of Australian industries, and aims to ensure a fair, safe, healthy and competitive Australia. We provide assurance that Australia’s measurement system is fit for purpose and evolves in line with advances in science and technology and with the changing measurement needs of their stakeholders in government, industry, business, and research.

The branch where this role is situated plays an important role in ensuring Australian consumers and industry can rely on trusted measurements for fair trade in goods and services.  To ensure traders comply with the law and adopt correct measurement trading practices, we employ Trade Measurement Inspectors who check that measuring instruments (for example, weighing instruments, fuel dispensers and weighbridges) are accurate, and pre-packaged articles contain the correct amount of produce.

The Role:

Reporting to the Manager, Programs and Digital, the Risk Analyst will work collaboratively with internal and external stakeholders to build and embed an effective risk framework for all branch activities. You will work collaboratively across all sections of the branch and work closely with the Departments risk teams.

The role will focus on the development of a single, clearly articulated risk framework covering all branch activities. This will include the review of existing, and the development of new policies, procedures, templates and tools.

BASELINE SECURITY CLEARANCE NEEDED AS A MINIMUM

The Risk Analyst operates under broad direction and will be responsible for the following:

1.      Develop and implement a comprehensive risk management framework.

2.      Develop and review policies, procedures, risk management tools and templates.

3.      Manage, deliver and monitor projects.

4.      Share knowledge within the branch and the Department to improve risk maturity.

5.      Foster an environment of continuous improvement by keeping abreast of industry and government best practice and proactively engaging with stakeholders to deliver outcomes.

6.      Demonstrate behaviour according to APS code of conduct and department standards and participate fully in all aspects of WH&S

Key Capabilities:

The capabilities listed below describe the specific skills, knowledge and behaviours required to successfully perform this job role:

1.      Demonstrated ability to develop and implement effective risk frameworks within a government or regulatory setting, including the development of policies, procedures, templates and tools.

2.      Demonstrated experience in developing and leading projects across multiple business units. 

3.      Highly developed written and oral communication skills, including a demonstrated ability to document and present complex risk information in a clear and concise manner.

4.      Demonstrated ability to develop and maintain strong productive and collaborative working relationships with stakeholders.

5.      Well-developed skills in research, analysis and problem-solving.

6.      Sound knowledge of, or the ability to rapidly acquire a sound knowledge of branch activities, legislation, resource management guides, policies and procedures.

Mandatory Requirements:

·       Australian Citizenship.

·       BASELINE SECURITY CLEARANCE NEEDED AS A MINIMUM

Desirable Requirements:

·       A relevant degree or higher qualification.

·       Project Management qualifications and/or experience.

·       Experience in contemporary database interrogation, analysis and reporting software.

·       Ability to quickly gain sound operational knowledge of Acts and associated regulations.
